# Mini App Frontend

## Structure

- `src/game/` — engine, constants, audio (no DOM)
- `src/lib/telegram.ts` — WebApp SDK wrapper
- `src/lib/api.ts` — fetch calls to Railway API
- `src/lib/branding.ts` — Prompt Anatomy co-branding (`VITE_PROMPT_ANATOMY_URL`)
- `src/lib/effects.ts` — visual effects (reduced-motion aware)
- `src/app.ts` — UI controller and DOM wiring
- `src/template.ts` — HTML shell
- `src/style.css` — design tokens and utilities

## Rules

- Never embed `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` or Supabase keys in client code.
- Use `getInitData()` for all authenticated API calls.
- Leaderboard tabs: Daily and Weekly only (v1).
- Share: prefer `Telegram.WebApp.shareMessage()`, fallback to clipboard.
- Styling: Tailwind utility classes via Vite plugin; no CDN Tailwind in production.
- Game logic changes must maintain parity with [snippet.txt](../../snippet.txt) unless spec updated.

## Shipped mechanics guardrails (v1.6)

See [ROADMAP.md](../../ROADMAP.md) § Shipped baseline. Do not regress without spec update:

- Rank-gated obstacles: Meeting (Intern) → Reorg (Manager+) → Deadline (`burnout` type, CEO+)
- Intern tutorial ramp: lower spawn rate first 12 rungs; guaranteed coffee by rung 8 if none collected
- Reorg fairness: next rung (`rungs[1]`) exempt from swap during reorg ticks
- 2s energy drain pause on promotion
- HUD milestone chip; game-over death cause + retry tips
- Code type `burnout` vs UI label **Deadline** — see [docs/mvp-scope.md](../../docs/mvp-scope.md) terminology table

Do not add Legends tab or new control schemes without scope approval.

## Local Dev

```bash
cd apps/mini-app && npm run dev
```

Set `VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8000` in root `.env`.
